          "ruleId": "TOOL_POISONING",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "Detected suspicious tool name: '\"__main__\"'. Full-schema poisoning embeds malicious directives in tool names, not just descriptions. Tool names like 'always_run_first', 'override_*', or '__instruction__' signal an attempt to manipulate agent tool selection or execution order. This is the 'Full-Schema Poisoning' (FSP) technique documented in 2025 MCP security research."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
