          "fixes": [
            {
              "description": {
                "text": "1. Bind to 127.0.0.1 for localhost-only access:\n   Python:  host='127.0.0.1'\n   Go:      net.Listen(\"tcp\", \"127.0.0.1:8080\")\n   Node.js: server.listen(8080, '127.0.0.1')\n2. If external access is required, bind to a specific interface IP\n3. Use a reverse proxy (nginx, caddy) to front the service with TLS and auth\n4. In containers: if 0.0.0.0 is intentional, ensure the container network\n   is not exposed to the public internet and authentication is enforced\n5. Add authentication middleware before exposing any MCP HTTP endpoints"
