          "ruleId": "SSRF",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "Hardcoded cloud metadata service endpoint detected: 'result = await capture.call(\"fetch_url\", url=\"http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/\")'. The AWS Instance Metadata Service (169.254.169.254), GCP metadata (metadata.google.internal), and Azure IMDS are accessible from cloud instances. If an SSRF vulnerability exists anywhere in the server, attackers can use these endpoints to steal cloud credentials (IAM roles, service account tokens). This finding may indicate the server is aware of and interacts with metadata services."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "tests/test_advanced.py",
